English Summary

Velvet Commotion and Organizational Change

Part 1 - Organizational Change:

The organizational landscape in Armenia underwent a remarkable transformation in 2017. Beyond the spike in NGO registrations, there was also a 50% increase in the number of registered foundations compared to previous years. Most strikingly, 112 new media outlets were registered in 2017, a figure that dwarfed the near-zero registrations in other years. This unprecedented growth in civil society organizations and media outlets raises questions about the factors driving this change, including the possibility of external support and its implications for Armenias political future.

Part 2 - Velvet Commotion:

In 2017, Armenia experienced an unprecedented surge in civil society activity, dubbed the velvet commotion. This period saw a dramatic increase in the registration of NGOs, foundations, and media outlets. Notably, 1,029 NGOs were registered in 2017, four times more than in 2016, with half of these registered in December alone. This sudden burst of civic engagement set the stage for the Velvet Revolution that would unfold in 2018, demonstrating how grassroots movements can catalyze significant political change.
